feat(deps): auto-detect internal repos from project gradle files

User no longer needs to manually fill "Internal repos" in Settings - the
plugin scans build.gradle, build.gradle.kts, settings.gradle in the
project root and direct subprojects, extracts every URL declared inside
maven { url ... } or shorthand maven("..."), and treats anything that's
not a known public repo (Maven Central, Google, Gradle Plugin Portal,
Spring, Jitpack, JBoss, Sonatype OSS) as internal.

Manual override still wins: if the Settings field is non-empty, that list
is used unchanged.

Bug found by the new test: stripLineComment() was killing "//" inside
URL schemes (https://...), so detection returned empty for every file.
Fixed: only strip "//" when it's not preceded by ":".

Tests: RepoDetectorTest - 14 cases on real Gradle file fixtures:
- Groovy DSL: maven { url '...' }, shorthand maven '...'
- Kotlin DSL: maven { url = uri('...') }, shorthand maven('...')
- settings.gradle pluginManagement repositories
- Multi-module: detection across subprojects
- Public repos excluded
- Commented-out URLs ignored without breaking schemes
- Realistic onyx-platform fixture with Spring milestone + nexus mix
- Detected substrings round-trip into DepsScanner.matchesInternalRepo
- Edge cases: empty project, missing dir, deduplication, weird URLs
